name: opensearch-sentiment-analyzer
description: This project implements a sentiment analysis system for OpenSearch, automatically analyzing and scoring the sentiment of customer reviews as they are ingested into the customer_reviews index.

name: Springboot-Microservice
description: A mini e-commerce system built with Spring Boot, demonstrating microservice architecture concepts from Spring Microservices in Action by Kalpit Patel and John Carnell. The project includes multiple microservices. leveraging Spring Cloud, API Gateway, and service discovery to create a scalable and resilient e-commerce platform

name: DrivePro
description: A microservices-based distributed chauffeur management system with Spring Boot

name: payment-processing-microservices
description: A clean and scalable backend system for payment processing, designed with microservices architecture. It includes user management, order tracking, notification handling, and optional fraud detection. Built for high performance and easy deployment with Docker and Kafka.

name: Microservices_Shop
description: This project is a microservices-based web API inspired by Microsoft Shop, built with C# and .NET. It features shopping cart management, discount coupons, and more. Using Entity Framework Core, Pomelo, and Swagger, the system is designed to be scalable, modular, and robust, showcasing best practices in modern e-commerce architecture.

name: modme-microservices-clone
description: modme clone  is a gRPC-based microservice designed to manage and control the operations of learning centers. This service handles key functionalities such as managing students, courses, instructors, and scheduling, and it provides efficient communication between different services within the modme.uz system.

name: Hospital-Management-System
description: Microservices-based Healthcare Management System built with Java 17, Spring Boot, React, PostgreSQL, and Spring Security. Features Feign, Resilience4j, WebSocket, and JWT for robust and scalable operations.

name: Hotels-Rating-Project-with-Microservices
description: This project is a scalable and distributed Hotel Rating System built using the Microservices Architecture. It allows users to browse hotels, provide ratings, and view aggregated ratings. Each functionality is encapsulated in its own microservice, enabling modularity, scalability, and ease of maintenance.

name: FlawIS
description: Collection of microservices that implement conference registration system of Faculty of Law, Comenius University in Bratislava

name: book-service
description: A basic java microservice that deals with the book service functionality in the library management system

name: Kurkure-e-commerce
description: This is an e-commerce website created with microservices, integration with AI ML recommended system and we are using tech stack given as Front end Framework: REactJS state management: Redux styling:materialui,sass/scss backend:nodejs Backend framework: expressjs database:postgress firebase  cache :Redis Web SErver: Ngnix cloud AI/ML: Recommendation

name: hexagonal-architecture
description: This project is an eCommerce platform built using Hexagonal Architecture (also known as Ports and Adapters) and implemented with Spring Boot. The system follows a Microservices approach.

name: Exam-surveillance-platform
description: A modern exam surveillance management system built with Spring Cloud microservices and React. Streamlines exam planning and surveillance assignments at ENSA El Jadida with automated scheduling and comprehensive reporting.

name: EmergencyNotificationAPI
description: Emergency notification system for critical situations. The service allows users to send notifications to their social circle in case of emergencies in one click

name: uber-clone
description: This project is a backend implementation of a basic Uber clone using a microservices architecture. It consists of three distinct services: User, Captain, and Ride, each responsible for handling specific functionalities within the system.

name: SpringMappingCrud
description: This Category-Product Management System is built with Spring Boot using a microservices architecture to manage categories and products with CRUD operations. It includes server-side pagination, one-to-many relationships, and global exception handling with @ControllerAdvice.

name: SpringProjectMapping
description: This Category-Product Management System is built with Spring Boot using a microservices architecture to manage categories and products with CRUD operations. It includes server-side pagination, one-to-many relationships, and global exception handling with @ControllerAdvice.

name: EShop
description: A cloud-native e-commerce system built with ASP.NET Core, leveraging modern Microservices Architecture, .NET 8, and C# 12. Features include RabbitMQ, gRPC, YARP API Gateway, Redis, PostgreSQL, SQLite, and SQL Server. Implements CQRS, DDD, Vertical Slice Architecture, and Clean Architecture for scalability, maintainability, and best practices.

name: rbac
description: This project is a microservice developed in Python with the objective of implementing a Role-Based Access Control system. The primary goal is to manage and enforce access permissions based on roles assigned to users. The service provides secure and flexible access control for resources, ensuring that users can only perform actions permitted by role

name: I4_0_SMIA
description: This repository contains the ongoing development of a project that aims to achieve a I4.0 Standardized Microservice-based Industrial Agent (I4.0 SMIA) proposal. This development is performed by Ekaitz Hurtado within a PhD thesis at the University of the Basque Country (UPV/EHU) , specifically in the Control and Systems Integration research group.
